[2] Pakistan: violence comment
Date: Sat 7 Jan 2023
From: Prof. T Jacob John <tjacobjohn@yahoo.co.in> [edited]


Re: ProMED post Poliomyelitis update (02): WPV1 ES, cVDPV1 AFP & ES, cVDPV2 AFP & ES, violence 20230106.8707649

From the moderator's commentary in the above cited posting:
"The violence against polio vaccination workers including police officers protecting the actual vaccination teams is hard to fathom. In addition to the injured and killed individuals, in the long run the children suffer as seen by the increase in AFP cases associated with WPV1 infection during 2022."

Prof. John's comment in response:
The EPI schedule in Pakistan is 3 doses of pentavalent [5 antigen] vaccine (DPT, Hib and Hep B) and OPV at 6, 10 and 14 weeks (Imran H et al. Routine immunization in Pakistan: comparison of multiple data sources and identification of factors associated with vaccination. Int Health. 2018; 10: 84-91; https://doi.org/10.1093/inthealth/ihx067). The bone of contention between the militants and WHO is OPV by campaign. Both parties seem to be adamant -- a simple solution will be to replace pentavalent with hexavalent [6 antigen] vaccine (pentavalent plus IPV). Since IPV is exquisitely efficacious, OPV campaigns can be discontinued.

--
Communicated by:
Prof. T Jacob John
Retired Professor of Clinical Virology
Christian Medical College
Vellore, India
tjacobjohn@yahoo.co.in

[As always, we thank Prof. T Jacob John for his astute and provocative comments. The use of OPV has been the target of rumors and misinformation campaigns in both Pakistan and Afghanistan (and Nigeria as well). IPV so far has been "innocent." Hence, an additional "pro" in the OPV vs IPV debate. But as to whether IPV would remain free from rumors and misinformation campaigns, only time will tell. - Mod.MPP]
